==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Keloid
<hw>Ke"loid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>cheloid</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[F. <ets>k⟦eacute⟧lo⟦ium⟧de</ets>,
from Gr. <grk>chhlh`</grk> crab's claw + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>k⟦eacute⟧lo⟦ium⟧de</ets>, <ets>ch⟦eacute⟧lo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Applied to a variety of tumor forming hard, flat,
irregular excrescences upon the skin, or to keloid scar
tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keloid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Keloid
<hw>Ke"loid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>cheloid</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A keloid tumor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An abnormally large scar tissue growing at the site
of a cut or surgical incision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kelotomy</ent>⟦br⟧
